                  <handDesc><handNote>Ink is brownish-black, with red used for titles and initials and green introduced as further decoration on some initials</handNote>
                     
                     <handNote>The manuscript contains a variety of Serbian bookhands, with abundant ligatures and diacritics. While these bookhands share similarities, 
                        the work of several scribes can be identified on close examination; e. g., fols 115r—117v are in a different hand, and it seems likely that fols 7b-15 
                        were not orginally part of this manuscript because red is used for the medial point and the scribe does not deploy green for decoration, differentiating 
                        these folios from the rest of the manuscript. The text on fol. 27v is a later insertion and written in a less skilled style
                     </handNote></handDesc>
                  
